[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

Tables are used very often in XSL-FO, since they are not only used for the usual purposes (multi-column lists), but also for layout purposes. If multi-line contents are to be placed next to each other, they are typically placed in a table.

## Insert table
- Drag the table icon into the template

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select format: "Without style": Table without borders, "Basic Style": Table with thin borders and light gray color

- Select and click the desired number of rows and columns.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Fill table
Each cell automatically contains a block. So you can click into the cells and enter text, or you can select the block in the outline and then enter the text.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

To insert other elements such as images, data fields etc., drag them onto the cell. Cells can be filled with any elements, including block-level elements.

On a logical level, the individual table cells are contained in the table rows, which are subordinated to the "table body" element.

## Mark table and table parts
Select the desired element in the outline. Alternatively, you can select table sections directly in the editor with the following procedure:

Mark table: Click on the table at any position, then click on the circle on the left above the table.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Mark columns/rows: Click on the table at any position, then click on the ::-icon in the column/row title.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note:

*It is not possible to select multiple columns or rows at once.*

Select cell: click on the cell in **the outline**.

Select block: click **on **the cell or click on the block in the outline.

## Change table structure
Add columns/rows: First click somewhere in the table. The small gray dots above and to the left of the table are used to add columns or rows inside the table. Use the + icon on the right or the bottom to add columns or rows at the end.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Delete columns/rows/table: Mark column, row or entire table (circle icon), delete with trashcan icon.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note:

*Single cells cannot be deleted or added as this would result in an irregular table structure.*

Merge cells: Right click on a cell and select "Merge Cell Right" or "Merge Cell Down". This will merge all affected content into one cell.

> Note:

*You can also use the number-columns-spanned or number-rows-spanned attributes to merge cells - if a cell is selected, these can be found under Style &amp; Properties *&gt; *Advanced *&gt; *Table*.

Split cells: You can also split a merged cell: Right click on the cell and select "Split cell". The contents will be placed in the first cell and may have to be moved again.

## Define column widths
For the selected column or for all columns if the whole table is selected, you can define the column width under *Style &amp; Properties *&gt; *Table *attribute *Column Width*.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

With version 6.3 you can pick the column border and drag it in order to change the width.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Define line heights
For the selected column or for all columns if the whole table is selected, you can define the column height under *Style &amp; Properties *&gt; *Table *attribute *Column Height*. The line height will be fixed, independent of the content.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The line height is automatically based on the content if no value is defined (by default),

## Border
When inserting the table, depending on the settings, a "Basic style" is already applied (see above), i.e. all table cells are surrounded by a thin grey border.

To set or change borders, select the desired table sections and then edit the settings under

*Style &amp; Properties *&gt; *Border*.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

There are two methods:

- First select the color, type and thickness of the frame and then click the buttons below to set the respective frame.

![](data:image/png;base64,)Meaning of the buttons: 

all borders outside

borders bottom and top

borders left and right

delete borders

border bottom

border top

border left

border right

You can also remove the respective borders by clicking these buttons again.

- First click on the desired border positions in the preview (between the corner boundaries!) then select color, type and width.

## Other formats, style sheets
For table elements, the background color and the vertical alignment are available for quick assignment. All other table-specific formats possible in XSL-FO can be found under *Style &amp; Properties *&gt; *Advanced *&gt; *Table*.

> Note

*Do not change the background color of the whole table on the "Table" element. If you want to change the background color of the table, set it on the "table body" element or table colum/row.*

The contents of a table (blocks with text, graphics, etc.) can be formatted using the attributes available for the corresponding element. Make sure to assign formats consistently, especially in case of formats which are applicable on multiple levels. For example, set the background color either always on the blocks or always on the cells.

Table style sheets:

You can also create style sheets for table formats. The creation and assignment is the same as for text style sheets.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

*Templates can only be assigned to cells individually, not to entire rows or columns.*

## Troubleshooting
Errors in table structures can result in a document not being rendered. When trying to create a PDF, "General error" will be displayed.

The most common source of errors in tables are contradictory row or column structures, which can result from merging cells, especially when working with the attributes number- columns-spanned or number-rows-spanned.

Another possible error is an empty row or empty cells copied into a repetition or condition without being contained in a column.

Pay attention to clean table structures. If necessary, insert a new table and move the contents as required.

Possible problems are displayed in the Error and Events window (![](data:image/png;base64,)-icon).
